OL,3,C'They were equal' - The women at the
OL,4,Ccoalface of the miners' strike
OL,6,F"The women weren't behind the men,
OL,7,Fthey were beside the men. They stood
OL,8,Ftogether. They were equal." - Heather
OL,9,FWood.
OL,11,FFor every one of the 23,000 men on
OL,12,Fstrike from the North East coalfields,
OL,13,Fthere was likely a mother, aunt, wife,
OL,14,Fchild or children who would have have
OL,15,Ffelt its effect.
OL,17,FNo work meant no pay, but houses still
OL,18,Fneeded heating and mouths still needed
OL,19,Ffeeding.
