OL,3,C'They were equal' - The women at the
OL,4,Ccoalface of the miners' strike
OL,6,FHeather Wood lived in Easington, a pit
OL,7,Fvillage in East Durham, where life was
OL,8,Fbuilt around the mine.
OL,10,FShe experienced first-hand the full
OL,11,Fforce of the strike between the
OL,12,FMarches of 1984 and 1985, and the
OL,13,Fchallenges it brought.
OL,15,FSpeaking to ITV Tyne Tees now, Heather
OL,16,Fsaid she "knew what was happening in
OL,17,Fevery house" and it broke her heart.
OL,19,F"It broke my heart because these were
OL,20,Fgood people, strong people," she
OL,21,Fcontinued.
