OL,3,C'They were equal' - The women at the
OL,4,Ccoalface of the miners' strike
OL,6,FInitiatives like Heather's soon grew
OL,7,Finto women-led support groups across
OL,8,Fthe North East.
OL,10,FIn Seaham, the group there was a
OL,11,Flifeline for Mary Stratford, whose
OL,12,Fhusband was a miner on strike, and for
OL,13,Fwhom, with a toddler in tow, every day
OL,14,Fwas a struggle.
OL,16,F"Life was difficult," she told ITV
OL,17,FTyne Tees. "Fuel was the problem all
OL,18,Fthrough the strike.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/10
