OL,3,C'They were equal' - The women at the
OL,4,Ccoalface of the miners' strike
OL,6,F"Trying to keep the house warm, trying
OL,7,Fto be warm, when you've got a little
OL,8,Fone was a daily nightmare.
OL,10,F"It (the support group) sustained me.
OL,11,FI think that's the best word I can
OL,12,Fthink of (for) that group....I would
OL,13,Fgo to those meetings and I would feel
OL,14,Fthis sense of belonging and
OL,15,Fsolidarity."
OL,17,FIn March 1985, the men went back to
OL,18,Fwork. They, and the women, may not
OL,19,Fhave won their fight against the pit
OL,20,Fclosures, but it instilled something
OL,21,Fin the women that has never been lost.
