OL,3,C'They were equal' - The women at the
OL,4,Ccoalface of the miners' strike
OL,6,FGina Lilburn, Ann's daughter, said:
OL,7,F"She was a miner's wife, and a miner's
OL,8,Fmother and a miner's daughter. That
OL,9,Fwas what drove my mum. The men would
OL,10,Fnever have been able to stay out.
OL,12,F"They wouldn't have been able to
OL,13,Fmanage without the support of the
OL,14,Fwomen. They would have starved. The
OL,15,Fwomen kept it going. I'm just so
OL,16,Fproud. She came into her own."
OL,18,FGina and Ann's granddaughter Kiki Lye
OL,19,Fis now in talks with Woodhorn Museum,
OL,20,Fnear Ashington, about incorporating a
OL,21,Fmemorial to her.
