OL,3,C'They were equal' - The women at the
OL,4,Ccoalface of the miners' strike
OL,6,F"She's a local hero - a national
OL,7,Fhero," said Kiki. "Everybody needs to
OL,8,Fknow how powerful the WAPC were, what
OL,9,Fthey did, the efforts they went to,
OL,10,Fjust so you can see what you can
OL,11,Fachieve when you don't agree with the
OL,12,Fgovernment.
OL,14,F"Sometimes you don't just sit back,
OL,15,Fyou've got to make a noise, you've got
OL,16,Fto shout out - don't be frightened to
OL,17,Fstand up for what you believe in and
OL,18,Fwhat you think is right."
