OL,3,C'They were equal' - The women at the
OL,4,Ccoalface of the miners' strike
OL,6,FForty years on and women with roots in
OL,7,Fthe region's mining heritage are still
OL,8,Fmaking a noise.
OL,10,FOn Saturday 1 March, Heather and many
OL,11,Fother members of the National Women
OL,12,FAgainst Pit Closures staged a rally
OL,13,Fthrough Durham to celebrate the role
OL,14,Fwomen played during the long months of
OL,15,Fthe miners' strike.
OL,17,FHeather continued: "Whatever those
OL,18,Fwomen went on to do, or not to do,
OL,19,Ftheir views, their opinions changed.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/10
